  "doc_id": "28616",
  "text": "It has been claimed (St. Jeor et al. 1974; [CITATION_1] unpublished data) that the semi-conservative DNA synthesis of the HCMV-infected cells is stimulated. Furukawa et al. (1976) found, however, that much of the early stimulation of DNA synthesis is due to an increased rate of mitochondrial DNA synthesis. Studies on the nature of the stimulated host DNA in cells infected with MCMV and simian CMV have not been published.",
  "correct_citation": {
